{"author":{"id":"783b610f274a0d93f6239db0fc75d0982606c877a4661d3aea84b42bc3a85cea"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1503458670,"nonce":"AsrLJSxaV6a5NpjQuGmzzM24r7U=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWUyNTIxNDg4NDQ=","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/1445","origin":"github"},"title":"Usage: Modify sam_dump.xml to avoid conflicting params that result in failures","message":"Tool: Download and Extract Reads in BAM format from NCBI SRA (Galaxy Version 2.8.1.2)\n\nIt is possible to choose BAM output and in the same job to also to choose _to not_ output a header. This always results in a failed job with an ambiguous failure message (invalid data format is the root cause).\n\nThe suggestion is to do one of these or another alternative that meets the same goal (prevent this use-case from being submitted as a valid job).\n\n 1 - modify the way the tool form is modeled (only have header option available when SAM is chosen? on main form or in advanced section) \n\n 2 - or to have the job abort with a pop-up stating the parameter conflict (\"Sam output must with used with the option to not include a header\" or similar). \n\nThe first seems better but either would be enough and someone else may have a preferred solution?\n\nWhile this is changed, it would also be nice if rerun for the tool left the advanced parameter section expanded when the original job had the advanced parameters changed from default - or - had the advanced section expanded at the time of the original job's submission (the usual method). For this tool/version, the advanced parameter section does not remain expanded at rerun. This is different than most other tool's usage during a rerun and in effect \"hides\" advanced setting changes that may have been made.\n\nGraphic of parameters: \n\n\u003cimg width=\"763\" alt=\"screen shot 2017-08-22 at 7 58 58 pm\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/8999735/29597128-79f48f62-8775-11e7-8e9c-be3502dbdda1.png\"\u003e","files":null}]}